igh and Muir- eadhach. O'Reilly, however, renders the Irish word muireadach 'a sovereign, a lord j also a man's name, Morogh.' It means rather l admiral,' literally protector of the sea; from muir the sea, eadhach protector. I derive the British name from mawreddwg, mawreddig, magnificent, great, from mawr, great."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Eva","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Popular Latinate form of   Eve  , used also as an Anglicization of the Irish name Aoife ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"verch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Orlo.","German: variant of   Ferch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferch","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eva verch Meredydd was born about 1391, in Wales, her father, Meredydd Ap Llywarch, was 250 and her mother, Mrs. Meredydd ap Llywarch, was 246. She married Einion Sais \"The Saxon\" ap Davydd from 1407 to 1439. They were the parents of at least 5 sons."},"et":{"1391–":"umbes 1391–Surnud","1391–Female":"umbes1391–Surnud","1376–1415":"1376–1415","1404–Male":"1404–Surnud","1408–Male":"1408–Surnud","1410–Male":"1410–Surnud","1415–1465":"1415–1465","–1465":"–1465","1143–Male":"1143–Surnud","1147–Female":"1147–Surnud","ABT    1410":"umbes 1410","1143":"1143","ABT    1408":"umbes 1408","1391":"umbes 1391","ABT    1404":"umbes 1404","from 1407 to 1439":"1407 kuni 1439","1415":"1415","1404":"1404","1147":"1147","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","1376":"1376","1408":"1408","Bodorgan, Anglesey, Wales":"Bodorgan, Anglesey, Wales","Wales":"Wales","of Bodorgan,Llangadwaladr,Anglesey,Wales":"Bodorgan, Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom","of,Llandyfryd